The paper discusses the potential of interactive knowledge maps for information seeking purposes, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the workshop also aimed to bring together experts in Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL), which are related sub-categories. The use of interactive knowledge maps also involves issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social implications (cs.SI), which are also possible sub-categories.
